Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Adjust racks to top and middle positions. Arrange @bacon{4%ounce} in a single layer on a separate baking sheet. Roast on middle rack until crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}. Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.

> Check often to avoid burning!

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium heat. Add onion, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add 1⁄4 cup water and @sugar{1%tsp} to pan with onion. Cook, stirring, until caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small serving bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Meanwhile, using the tip of a #spoon{}, remove and discard black gills from undersides of @portobello mushrooms{2}; trim any large stems if necessary. Halve mushrooms; thinly slice crosswise.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, @garlic powder{1%tsp} and @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a small serving bowl. Wipe out pan.

> Save remaining thyme for later.

While mushrooms cook, thinly slice @tomato{1}. Transfer to a #plate{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, @cheddar cheese{4%slice}, and @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} in separate #serving bowls{}. Arrange family style along with jammy onion, garlic mushrooms, tomato, and @sourdough bread{4%slice} for everyone to build their own sandwiches.

> You'll cook the sandwiches in the next step!

Arrange bacon family style along with other sandwich fillings.

Heat @butter{2%tbsp} in pan used for mushrooms over medium heat. Add sandwiches to hot pan (for 4 servings, you may need to work in batches, adding more butter between batches). Cook, covered, until bread is golden and butter is absorbed, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> Lower heat if browning too quickly.

Reduce heat to medium low. Flip sandwiches, adding an additional @butter{1%tbsp} to pan. Cook, covered, until bread is golden and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal. Serve with potato wedges and any remaining dressing on the side for dipping.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.